    "default_locale": "he",
    "description": {
        "he": "A ThunderBird extension to prevent the use of the Bcc field.\n\nBcc is the worst thing ever.\nIt kills transparency inside an organization.\nIf you use the Bcc feature, you should ask yourself why..\n\nEverytime you will add a recipient to the Bcc field, a small pop up will remind you that this is a potential spam and you should re-consider using this feature.\nYou can use the add on button to remove the recipient from the Bcc field before sending the email.\n\nThis can work well for organizations that use transparency as a way of life."
    },
